[src:gnu-autotools/autoconf-p04] New programs should use the POSIX function `setpgid`, which takes two process IDs as arguments (like the BSD `setpgrp`).
[src:gnu-autotools/autoconf-p04] Determine whether `stat` or `lstat` have the bug that it succeeds when given the zero-length file name as argument.
